body:
I understand the whole concept of Rencontres numbers but I can't understand how to prove this equation $$D_{n,0}=\left[\frac{n!}{e}\right]$$ where $[\cdot]$ denotes the rounding function (i.e., $[x]$ is the integer nearest to $x$ ). This equation that I wrote comes from solving the following recursion, but I don't understand how exactly the author calculated this recursion. $$\begin {align*} 
D_{n+2,0} & =(n+1)(D_{n+1,0}+D_{n,0}) \\
D_{0,0} & = 1 \\
D_{1,0} & = 0 
\end {align*}
$$
